column2: text
The Trump White House is considering resuming the use of 'negro' as a racial category.

Portugal doesn't have net neutrality regulations, and is an example of what happens without such laws; for example, a Portuguese telecommunications company, MEO, is parceling out access to specific broadband apps and content on a fee-for-service basis.
Taco Bell (or its owner) is the main financier of Alabama politician Roy Moore's Senate campaign.
As of August 2017, the Secret Service had run out of money for the year due to the demands of protecting President Trump and his family.
Queen Elizabeth contradicted London Mayor Sadiq Khan by 'refusing to retract' an invitation to Donald Trump to visit the UK.
Mitch McConnell said he would block the appointment of a special counsel to investigate Russian election interference
Green Card holders are being illegally registered to vote without their knowledge or consent in order to create legal grounds for their deportation.
President Donald Trump changed the constitution to read 'citizens' instead of 'persons.'
Pope Francis condemned Donald Trump for issuing a temporary travel ban in January 2017.
A video investigation showed that Planned Parenthood lies about providing prenatal care.
Tax reform plans proposed by House and Senate Republicans in November 2017 would remove the deduction for employee discounts.
Representative Frederica Wilson has never supported a bill intended to help military veterans.
The Trump International Hotel in Washington D.C. handed out flyers promoting an anti-CNN petition to guests at check-in.
There are currently 871 convicted felons playing for the NFL.
The actor Nora Kirkpatrick 'played' a victim as part of a fake terrorist bomb attack at Parsons Green in London.

The driver of the vehicle that killed one person and injured more than a dozen others at the Unite the Right rally in Charlottesville, Virginia, is a known 'radical leftist' supported by Hillary Clinton and George Soros.
Starbucks is giving a discount to undocumented immigrants on 11 August 2017.
In July 2017, President Trump dispatched federal investigators to the hamlet of Islamberg, New York, where they uncovered 'America's worst nightmare'.
Former Haitian official Klaus Oberwein died in a suspicious suicide days before he was scheduled to testify against either Hillary Clinton or the Clinton Foundation.
At an event in Warsaw on 6 July 2017, Polish First Lady Agata Kornhauser-Duda refused to shake hands with Donald Trump.
President Donald Trump hosted the National Rifle Association at the White House on the anniversary of the Sandy Hook massacre.
Former Alabama judge Roy Moore authored a chapter in a 2011 textbook arguing that women should not hold political office

After only nine months in office, President Trump and family had already spent $147 million on personal travel, amounting to one-and-a-half times as much as President Obama and family spent in the eight years of the latter's presidency.
Pro-Donald Trump activists were accosted by a 'violent mob' while eating pizza at a Chicano Park.
On 1 September 2017, a new law will come into force in Texas, making it harder for consumers to get paid for property insurance claims related to weather.
East Central University has been forced to remove a cross and other Christian symbols from their chapel.
Robert F. Kennedy Jr. said that “Trump could be the greatest president in history.”
In August 2017, the Texas House of Representatives passed a bill that would force women to purchase 'rape insurance.'
Then-Secretary of State Clinton ordered then-FBI Director Robert Mueller to deliver highly enriched uranium to the Russians in a secret plane-side meeting in 2009.
The Environmental Protection Agency awarded $100 million to Flint, Michigan, at the behest of President Trump.
Redesigned challenge coins given out by President Trump replaced the familiar 'E pluribus unum' motto with Trump's campaign slogan.
The Tax Cuts and Jobs Act of 2017 calls for eliminating or severely curtailing the personal casualty deduction for losses from wildfires and other natural disasters.
A pro football fan sat on the United States flag while wearing a shirt that read: 'I stand for the national anthem.'
The Department of Health and Human Services has scheduled web site maintenance for Healthcare.gov on most Sundays during Obamacare open enrollment.
In September 2017, U.S. Virgin Islands Governor Kenneth Mapp signed an executive order empowering the National Guard to seize weapons and other private property.
On 14 August 2017, protesters removed and destroyed the county flag from the Hennepin County, Minnesota jail, and temporarily replaced it with an Antifa flag.
The national debt saw a 'surprising' decline of $102 billion between 20 January and 27 July 2017.
Melania Trump 'liked' a tweet that poked fun at her relationship with her husband, President Donald Trump.
A plaque displayed on a golf course owned by President Trump commemorates a Civil War battle that never happened.
Canada, Norway, and Germany each offer federally paid family leave programs ranging from 35 weeks to 1 year in length. <BR>
The Senate GOP tax reform bill includes a tax cut for private jet owners.
Author Ingersoll Lockwood wrote the books 'Baron Trump's Marvelous Underground Journey' and '1900: or, The Last President'  in the 1890s.
In March 2017, Oklahoma State Representative George Faught said rape and incest are the 'will of God.'
President Trump played golf six times during his first month in office despite frequently criticizing his predecessor's golfing habits.
Adolf Hitler said that the only way that the Nazi party could have been stopped was if it were destroyed in its infancy.
Colorado has offered free birth control for five years, leading to: a 40 percent drop in unintended pregnancy, a 42 percent drop in abortions, and millions of dollars in healthcare savings.
The House passed a bill that allows government contractors to discriminate against lesbian, gay, bisexual and transgender people.
Mike Pence once said that condoms are 'too modern' and 'too liberal' and offer a poor defense against sexually transmitted diseases.
Three countries issued travel warnings to their citizens about visits to the United States.
Donald Trump's ancestors changed their surname from 'Drumpf' to 'Trump.'
Donald Trump wins the 2016 United States presidential election.
Bernie Sanders robbed  Hillary Clinton of the Democratic nomination.
